athletes.Name: Taylor Warne
athletes.Biography: Hi my name is Taylor Warne! I’m a fifth year softball player at Purdue University Fort Wayne, and a first generation college graduate. I’m currently getting my masters degree in Management. This last may I got my Bachelors degree in Management as well. In 2018 I started my college career at Menlo College in the bay area of California. My sophomore year was cut short due to COVID, and in December of my Junior year I decided to transfer to find an institution that would allow me to use my extra year of eligibility to earn a masters degree. I then transferred to Lake Land College in January where I earned my associates in 7 months. I’m currently a intern at Barnes and Thornburg Law Firm here in Fort Wayne. Following graduation I’m interested in Sports Marketing and management, as well as Medical Sales.

athletes.Name: Wilmer Hernandez
athletes.Biography: Wilmer Janiel Hernández Torres is currently a student-athlete and senior in the Purdue Fort Wayne Men’s Volleyball program. He was born and raised in Puerto Rico where he had the opportunity to represent the island as the Youth National Men’s Volleyball team captain in various international tournaments. He is currently finishing a Bachelor’s degree in Biology with a concentration in Microbiology and Immunobiology along with an Associate’s in Chemical Methods and a minor in Spanish with the goal of applying to medical school in Puerto Rico for the upcoming cycle. During his three years at PFW, he is a:- - - (x1) Top 50 student- - (x3) Academic All-MIVA Honor student - - (x3) Dean’s & Semester Honors List student- - He also serves as the Vice-President of SALT (Student-Athlete Leadership Team), a member of the National Society of Leadership and Success, a member of the American Society of Microbiology, a member of the MedLife club, and he is the campus captain for The Hidden Opponent.- View more...

athletes.Biography: My name is Mason Frazier. I’m employed as a fulltime server during the summer months at Broken Rocks Cafe and Bakery in Wooster, OH. As a server, my main goal is to ensure every customer I have the privilege of serving has the best dining experience possible. Customer service is my top priority. If customers leave happy, then I’m personally fulfilled.- - In the Fall and Spring I am a fulltime college student studying to obtain a bachelor's degree in marketing. I am also a member of the men's golf team. Being part of a NCAA Division 1 team has helped me become better with time management. There are various activities related to golf that require much time investment such as: physio training, practice, university leadership meetings, and travel. - - In the future I plan to work in the business side of the food service industry. Through the skill of knowing what the customer wants, I will be able to sell to anyone. Likewise, having good teamwork skills enables me to work with anyone.- View more...

My unofficial minors - I spend a lot of my free time learning about them - are biology and health.
